#include <stdio.h>

int main(void) {
    printf("hello, world\n");
    return 0;
}


The tradition of printing 'hello, world' in programming examples stems from its use as the simplest possible program to demonstrate a language's basic syntax and structure. It was popularized by Brian Kernighan and Dennis Ritchie in 'The C Programming Language' (1978) and has since become a universal first program for beginners across languages.
